Boolean :

The boolean (not Boolean) is a primitive data type in JavaScript.
 It can have only two values: true or false. 
 It is useful in controlling program flow using conditional statements like ,
 if else, switch, while loop, etc.

 <html>
<body>
	<h1>Demo: JavaScript Boolean</h1>
	<script>
		var YES = true;
		var NO = false;

		if(YES)
		{
			alert("This code block will be executed");
		}

		if(NO)
		{
			alert("This code block will not be executed");
		}
    </script>
</body>
</html>